name: Test -> load module input terminals,
description: Measure the voltage at the load module input terminals (before the diode) both during normal lamp operation and during the brief 'off' phase to verify if the voltage reaching the load module is stable or if there is an intermittent drop., outcome="Voltage at 'Load Input Cable (+)' is 0.3592 V, and voltage at 'Load Input Cable (−)' is 0.0003 V. No polarity inversion is detected in these connections. Voltage at the load input appears to be steady during the measurement phases.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> control module cable connections (at terminals),
description: Visually inspect the fast-connection wiring between the control module and the load module to check for possible wiring or connection errors, such as swapped or incorrectly attached cable pairs., outcome="All control and load cables were visually inspected and no observable internal faults were found. The 'Control Output' and 'Load Input' cables are labeled for positive and negative polarity. There is no explicit evidence of polarity inversion or swapped connections reported in these observations.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> load module diode,
description: Test the voltage immediately before and after the diode in the load module during lamp operation to determine if the diode is blocking current or causing a voltage drop., outcome='The voltage across the load protection diode shows 0.3592 V at the anode and 0.0003 V at the cathode, indicating a forward voltage drop typical for a conducting diode. The voltage across the main load (lamp) terminals is approximately 0 V, suggesting little or no potential difference across the lamp.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=45.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control module switched cable indicator (LED),
description: Monitor the switched cable indicator LED in the control module during operation to see if it behaves normally (steady on) or also shows the periodic on/off effect, which could help isolate whether the issue is before or after the control module output., outcome='The Control Module Inspection Panel was successfully observed, and no internal faults were found during visual inspection. The panel provides probe access for further testing without cube rotation.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=10.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control module switched cable indicator (LED),
description: Test the voltage across the switched cable indicator LED and directly observe its on/off behavior during the periodic lamp outage. Record both the voltage and the state of the LED at those times to determine if it is switching off in sync with the lamp, indicating a disruption within the control module, or if it remains on, indicating the fault is further downstream., outcome='The measured voltage at the PSU Status LED (green) anode is 1.2916 V, and the cathode is at 0.0 V. The LED is visibly lit, with no observable internal faults.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> load module lamp indicator bulb,
description: Test the voltage across the lamp indicator bulb in the load module during both the on and off periods of the main lamp. This will help determine if any current is flowing through the indicator bulb, providing insight into whether the fault is with the main bulb or elsewhere., outcome='Voltage across the internal indicator lamp is 0.0003 V in both directions, indicating no significant voltage present. This suggests that little or no current is flowing through the indicator bulb.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
